    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-24T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-24T10:00:00-05:00" n="638"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d638">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 033.4120</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-24T16:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 9.08 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9684. <persName corresp="#p_DBSM1">Sir Maurice de Bunsen</persName>, formerly
                    British Ambassador at Vienna, who has been acting during the war as extra
                    assistant under secretary at the Foreign Office, left last week for South
                    America on a mission the nature of which I understand has been communicated to
                    you by Lord <persName corresp="#p_RERDI1">Reading</persName>.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d638fn1">See telegrams to the Ambassador in Great Britain, No. 7761,
                        May 16, and from the Ambassador in Great Britain, No. 10106, May 17, <hi
                            rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_689">pp. 689</ref> and <ref
                            target="#pg_690">690</ref>, respectively.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
